Assailants beat up a Zairean asylum-seeker  in this eastern city Monday and roughed up a woman who had tried to intervene,  police said.
One of the attackers shouted the "negro must be beaten to a pulp,"  witnesses said.
They threw a 23-year-old woman to the ground when she tried to help the  Zairean man.
The assailants fled before the arrival of police forces.
